# agentic-scaffold — Cursor Rules

## Project
- Name: agentic-scaffold
- Type: Cowork plugin (Claude Desktop)
- Stack: Markdown templates + SKILL.md workflow specification

## Conventions
- Read CLAUDE.md at session start for full project conventions
- Log architectural decisions in DECISIONS.md before implementing
- Update CHANGELOG.md after significant work sessions
- Capture future ideas in ROADMAP.md — items flow to DECISIONS.md when evaluated
- README.md is human-facing; CLAUDE.md is agent-facing — keep them distinct

## Templates
- Template files live in `templates/` and use `{{variable}}` interpolation
- Variables: project_name, description, stack, directory_structure, stack_conventions, date, year, license
- Every template has a source attribution footer comment
- Changing a variable name requires updating the interpolation table in skills/init/SKILL.md

## SKILL.md
- Description field follows CSO pattern: trigger on conditions, never summarize the workflow
- YAML frontmatter with name and description fields
- Workflow must be fully self-contained

## Plugin Packaging
- Package: `zip -r agentic-scaffold.plugin .` from plugin root
- Exclude: .git/, .DS_Store, node_modules/
- Version in plugin.json must match latest CHANGELOG.md entry

## Key Principles
- Zero runtime dependencies
- Never overwrite user files — always present and get approval first
- Progressive disclosure — don't front-load complexity
- Layered generation — 5 core files always, adaptive files based on tooling/team
- Eat your own cooking — this repo uses its own scaffold pattern
